<HEADLINE> Armenia's Prosecutor General Shot Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Armenian Prosecutor General Genrik
Khachatryan was shot and killed in his office Thursday, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The killer was identified as Aram Karapetyan, a former
transport prosecutor, Tass said in a dispatch from Yerevan, the
Armenian capital.
</P>
<P>
Karapetyan committed suicide after killing the 59-year-old
prosecutor general. His motive has yet to be established.
</P>
<P>
Police have cordoned off the Prosecutor General's office and
nearby buildings, Tass said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
