<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bonn: U.S. Criticism on German Bosnian Refugee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- German Interior Minister Manfred
Kanther Thursday said United States accusations were absurd that
Germany was forcing back Bosnian refugees.
</P>
<P>
Kanther said Bonn was not trying to forcibly speed up the
repatriation of Bosnian refugees, noting that the government based
the repatriation policy on voluntary return.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by Ministry spokesman Detlef Dauke as saying the
accusations from Washington as "absurd".
</P>
<P>
Germany received some 350,000 Bosnian war refugees in all and
still has 140,000 of them. In the first seven months of this year,
it repatriated some 75,000 refugees. German officials said of them
only 1,200 were forcibly expelled and many of these people had
been convicted criminals.
</P>
<P>
The officials conceded, however, that some refugees from the
Serb-controlled Republika Srpska were returning to other areas of
Bosnia as the first step to going home.
</P>
<P>
U.S. officials described Germany's repatriation of Bosnian
refugees as refugee "dumping", which they said ran against the
agreed policy of sending refugees back to their former homes.
</P>
<P>
They voiced concern over Germany's practice, saying it
threatened the hard-won Bosnian peace process.  
</P>
</TEXT>
