<HEADLINE> China Urges Protection for Ethnic Chinese Women in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- China's leading women's
organization today called on the Indonesian government to adopt
effective measures to protect the legal rights of the ethnic
Chinese women.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued today, the All-China Women's Federation
(ACWF) criticized criminal acts committed against ethnic Chinese
women during the recent riots in Indonesia. The organization
voiced the strong indignation of women throughout China.
</P>
<P>
Social turmoil in Jakarta during May resulted in the
destruction of thousands of Chinese businesses, and the even more
horrifying is savage rape of ethnic Chinese women, according to
the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement stresses that the atrocities were grave
violations of the legal rights of women, and notes that the ACWF
and Chinese women as a whole are deeply concerned and sympathize
with the victims.
</P>
<P>
The federation called on the Indonesian government to deal
promptly with the facts and introduce immediate measures to
uphold justice for victims by conducting a thorough investigation,
severely punishing perpetrators and preventing the recurrence of
similar incidents.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has clearly stated its stance and
demanded that Indonesia protect the personel safety, legal rights
and interests of ethnic Chinese. Chinese societies and
organizations throughout the world have also expressed their
indignation over the atrocities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
