<HEADLINE> Sartaj to Be Appointed Pakistan's New FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Finance Minister
Sartaj Aziz Thursday confirmed the press reports that he is being
appointed foreign minister in place of Gohar Ayub Khan who has
tendered his resignation in April.
</P>
<P>
"Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif has formally asked me to look
after the Foreign Ministry. Now I am waiting for the official
notification," Sartaj told the private News Network International
(NNI) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said the notification might be issued anytime Thursday or
Friday but dispelled the impression given by the press that he was
being removed from the finance minister due to his failure to
manage the country's financial matters.
</P>
<P>
Sartaj said the prime minister took the decision in April this
year when Gohar decided to relinquish his charge as the foreign
minister.
</P>
<P>
Gohar, who has requested the prime minister to change his
present post, also confirmed that he will not perform duties as
foreign minister Friday, the NNI said.
</P>
<P>
"The prime minister has asked me to take any ministry of my
choice," Gohar was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Gohar had made the request as according to him the Foreign
Ministry keeps him away from his electorates.
</P>
<P>
Sartaj, 69, had served as finance minister from August 1990 to
July 19193 during the first government led by Prime Minister
Sharif and was given the same portfolio in Sharif's new cabinet,
which was sworn in in February 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
