<HEADLINE> Russia Will Guarantee Safe Transportation of Missiles to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Ambassador in Athens
Valentina Matvienko Thursday said that her country would guarantee
the safe transportation of S-300 anti-aircraft missiles to the
divided island of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Matvienko said this during her meeting with Greek Deputy
Foreign Minister Yannos Kranidiotis shortly before the latter's
departure for Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
She stressed that as an independent and sovereign state, Cyprus
had "inalienable right" to make decisions concerning its defense
programs.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Greek Cypriots-dominated south
and Turkish Cypriots-controlled north since 1974 when Turkish
troops landed and took over the northern third of the island in
the wake of a failed pro-Athens coup.
</P>
<P>
To strengthen its defense capacity, Cyprus has decided to
purchase the Russian-made S-300 missiles, which will be deployed
later this year. but Turkey has threatened to use force to stop
Nicosia's installation of the missiles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
