<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Factfile of Michelle Smith de Bruin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Following is the factfile of
Michelle Smith de Bruin, who was banned by the swimming world
governing body FINA on Thursday for tampering with a urine sample:
</P>
<P>
1969: born on December 16 in Dublin
</P>
<P>
1982: starts swimming competitively
</P>
<P>
1988: Olympic debut in Seoul in 100m and 200m backstroke, 200m
and 400m individual medley. National record in 200m backstroke.
1992 Graduates from University of Huston, Texas, in
communications. Competes in 200m medley and backstroke and 400m
medley in Barcelona Olympics.
</P>
<P>
1993: comes under wing of erik de Bruin, Dutch shot and discus
record-holder
</P>
<P>
1994: fifth in 200m butterfly at World Championships
</P>
<P>
1995: sets Irish records in 50m, 100m, 400m and 800m
freestyle,100m backstroke, 100m and 200m butterfly, 200m and 400m
medley. Wins short-course World Cup series. Ranked world No.1 in
200m butterfly over shorts course, sixth in 100m butterfly and
seventh in 200m medley. First Irishwoman to win European title in
200m butterfly and individual medley.
</P>
<P>
1996: marries de Bruin. No.1 in world 400m freestyle rankings,
a day after Olympic qualification date. Entry for Atlanta
initially rejected but succeeds on appeal. First Irish competitor
to win Olympic swimming medal and first Irish woman to win any
Olympic medal when she wins 400m medley. Follows up with gold in
400m freestyle and 200m individual medley, bronze in 200m
butterfly.
</P>
<P>
1997: two golds and two silvers at European championships in
Seville
</P>
<P>
April 29, 1998: FINA confirm she is under investigation over
allegations that drug-test sample tampered with.
</P>
<P>
May 25: FINA announce case will go before doping panel.
</P>
<P>
August 6: FINA annouce de Bruin banned for four years.
</P>
<P>
August 7: de Bruin says she will appeal and claim damage from
FINA.
</P>
</TEXT>
