<HEADLINE> Red Cross Collects Disaster Relief Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The China Red Cross Society
announced today that cash and in kind donations for flood relief
efforts in areas along the Yangtze River have hit 30 million
yuan (3.6 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, the areas are still in urgent need of medical supplies
to prevent the outbreak of epidemics and disinfectants to purify
drinking water, according to the society.
</P>
<P>
The International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent
Societies have raised some 9.68 million yuan for the China Red
Cross. The funds were mainly contributed by governments and Red
Cross societies in Canada, Britain, Denmark, Iceland, Norway, the
United States, Germany and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Five representatives from the International Federation of Red
Cross and Red Crescent Societies are in China to help draft
further relief plans for flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Local Red Cross societies in China and the Hong Kong Red Cross
Society have raised a total of 20 million yuan. The latter society
has already donated 600,000 yuan and plans to provide an
additional five million yuan in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The China Charity Federation joined the All-China Youth
Federation, All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, the
China Individual Laborers Association and various societies in
extensive fund-raising activities.
</P>
<P>
The federation has established a 24-hour donation hot line.
</P>
</TEXT>
