<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 250,000 People Evacuated in Jingjiang Flood Diversion Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- By 9:15 pm this evening, 250,000
residents in Jingjiang Flood Diversion Zone, in central China's
Hubei Province, have been evacuated to safe places, in preparation
for a possible diversion program to discharge flood waters.
</P>
<P>
The authorities plan to remove a total of 330,000 local
residents in the diversion zone, which is located in Gong'an
County, in order to protect major cities downstream.
</P>
<P>
Everything is in order there as the evacuation has been carried
out in a planned, organized manner. "The county town with dykes
built around is a safe place," says a local vendor, "so we are not
worried, and there is no price-hikes."  
</P>
