<HEADLINE> 120 Civilians, 10 Army Men Killed in Indian Firing: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 120 civilians and 10
Pakistani army men have been killed in the Indian firing during
the last week along the Line of Control, Pakistani Minister for
Kashmir Affairs Majid Malik said Friday.
</P>
<P>
During a briefing in Muzaffarabad, capital of Pakistan-held
Kashmir, Malik said that 400 civilians and 25 soldiers have also
been injured in the firing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 90 Indian soldiers have been killed in counterstrike
by the Pakistani army, he said.
</P>
<P>
The local government has taken a number of measures for relief
and rehabilitation of the affected people. It is reported that the
firing has rendered 55,000 people homeless and they have taken
shelter in camps.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the people at Garhidopatta near the Line of Control
Malik said that Pakistan is ready to counter any foreign
aggression. 
