<HEADLINE> U.S. Retailers Post Strong Sales for July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Most major retailers of the United
States posted strong sales in July, beating many estimates and showing
that the consumer still provides a strong underpinning to the
economy.
</P>
<P>
Results were strong accross nearly all retail categories, ranging
from discounters and department stores to specialty apparel and
electronics stores, according to statistics published by the Wall
Street Journal today.
</P>
<P>
Sales at stores open at least one year rose 5.7 percent in July, up
from 5.5 percent in the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Many retailers said that their results were above expectations, and
that despite July traditionally being a clearance month, they sold
more goods at full price.
</P>
<P>
The good performance was helped in part by solid sales in May and
June, which helped clear out inventories, leaving retailers more room
to bring in new seasonal and back-to school merchandise, which sold at
regular price.
</P>
<P>
All of this is a good sign for retail earnings for the fiscal
second quarter which for most retailers ended in July.
</P>
<P>
The first quarter also saw positive earnings for many U.S.
retailers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
