<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State-Owned Enterprises Urged to Strengthen Management on Laid-offs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- State-owned enterprises have been
instructed to standardize procedures for reducing their work
forces and providing basic subsistence for redundant workers.
</P>
<P>
The instructions were jointly issued by the Ministry of Labor
and Social Security, State Economic and Trade Commission, Ministry
of Finance, Ministry of Education, State Statistical Bureau and
All-China Federation of Trade Unions.
</P>
<P>
The six organizations jointly issued the circular covering
improved management over laid-off workers and the establishment of
reemployment service centers in state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The circular stipulates that spouses of laid-off workers, and
divorced or widowed spouses with minor children should be exempt
from work force reductions. The exemption also applies to the
disabled and spouses of soliders.
</P>
<P>
The circular requires that laid-off workers should receive
certificates from reemployment service centers in enterprises and
receive basic subsistence allowances.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises are required to establish reemployment service
centers and develop training plans.
</P>
<P>
The circular also calls for improved management of subsistence
payments for laid-offs workers and strictly prohibits the
misappropriation of such funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
