<HEADLINE> 400 Forest Fires Raging in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- About 400 forest fires raging in
British Columbia, west of Canada, have killed one person and left
hundreds of people homeless.
</P>
<P>
More than 170 new fires have broken out in the past week,
driving hundreds of people from their homes and putting another
1,000 on alert.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 soldiers from the Canadian Armed Forces joined
fire fighters to combat several major blazes Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The most seriously threatened community was Salmon Arm, 80
kilometers east of Kamloops in south-central British Columbia,
where a small fire tripled in size to 500 hectares in less than 24
hours due to winds up to 70 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
Winds continued to push the blaze toward Salmon Arm, which has
a population of 15,600.
</P>
<P>
The dry weather the province has endured for at least 21 days
and high temperatures exceeding 30 degrees centigrade are also
blamed for fueling the fires. 
</P>
