<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Goes Down This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai stock market has kept
the downward trend this week with a sharper drop compared with
last week, and B shares available for foreign citizens dropped to
a new low.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Composite Index on the Shanghai Stock Exchange
(SSE) ended the week at 1,271.07, down 3.48 percent on the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
The SSE-30 Index, which is based on 30 blue chips, edged down
2.68 percent to close at 3,215.13.
</P>
<P>
Indexes for real estate businesses fell the most, and those for
wholesale and retail businesses dropped the least.
</P>
<P>
The total transaction volume reached 16.05 billion yuan,
roughly the same as that of the previous week. Among the 459
stocks listed, 358 saw a transaction volume down and those of
only 93 went up.
</P>
<P>
B shares plummeted 5.4 percent from the previous week to ended
at 28.62 today. The transaction volume of B shares reached 194
million yuan, a slight rise from the previous week.
</P>
<P>
This week's trading volume for funds stood at 1.555 billion
yuan, 16 million yuan less than the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The bond market made brisk business this week, registering a
trading volume of 63.772 billion yuan, an increase of more than 50
percent from the previous week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
