<HEADLINE> Media Partners Distances Itself from Berlusconi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Sports marketing group Media
Partners confirmed on Friday that it was looking at plans for
European club soccer competitions and sought to distance itself
from Italian businessman Silvio Berlusconi.
</P>
<P>
It has been reported that a proposed European Super League was
instigated by Media Partners and its president Rodolfo Hecht did
have some links to the former Italian prime minister.
</P>
<P>
"Media Partners is constantly seeking ways of developing
various sports for the good of sporting clubs, players, supporters
and TV viewers. The company is currently examining proposals for
European club football competitions," it said in a statement
issued in London.
</P>
<P>
"These plans are still being developed and for this reason it
would be inappropriate to comment in any detail at this stage," it
added.
</P>
<P>
