speculation, Media Partners has no links with the media empire
controlled by Silvio Berlusconi."
</P>
<P>
However, two of the four-strong Media Partners management team
named in the statement have worked for Berlusconi's Fininvest
[FIN.CN] media and retail empire. Berlusconi has extensive TV
interests and is also the owner of former European champions AC
Milan.
</P>
<P>
Hecht was previously in charge of Fininvest's strategic
management of sports events while director Andrea Locatelli is a
former AC Milan player who worked in sports event production and
marketing at Fininvest.
</P>
<P>
Media Partners describes itself as an independent
company, wholly owned by its partners. It said it was not
affiliated to any sports federation or media group and had offices
in Milan, London and New York.
</P>
<P>
A number of leading European clubs including England's
Manchester United, Arsenal, Spain's Real Madrid and Dutch team
Ajax Amsterdam have admitted this week that they had been involved
in the talks of a breakaway competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
