Science and Technology, Xu Guanhua, told a national conference on
high-tech development zones here today that the Ministry will
discuss policies that allow high-tech ventures to be listed on the
stock exchange as early as possible.
</P>
<P>
China will start trial operations, Xu said, and believes that
listing high-tech ventures will help them solve their problems
with a shortage fund. The State Council has decided to offer
special funds and loans for developing high-tech ventures.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing and Shanghai governments are reported to have a
large amount of funds for inter-bank loan guarantees for this.
</P>
<P>
Xu says that his ministry is also set to draft regulations to
protect the rights and interests of scientists whose discoveries
are used by industry. China began a "Torch Program" in 1988 to
encourage the commercial and industrial use of scientific
discoveries.
</P>
<P>
China has 53 high-technology development zones with about
13,7000 high-tech ventures inside.  
