<HEADLINE> DPRK Praises Bangladesh for Rejecting U.S. Military Demand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) on Friday praised Bangladesh for refusing
to sign a "status of forces agreement" with the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh government's recent rejection of the U.S.
demand that the two countries sign the agreement would defend the
dignity and sovereignty of Bangladesh and was in its best
interests, a spokesman for the DPRK foreign ministry told the
state news agency KCNA.
</P>
<P>
The unilateral demand of the United States showed that it still
maintained its outdated policy of trying to deploy troops and
establishing military bases in other countries and regions, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The so-called "status of forces agreement" includes visa-free
entry of U.S. soldiers into Bangladesh, guarantee for unrestricted
activities of the U.S. forces and introduction into the country of
the equipment and supplies for the U.S. forces without customs
procedures. 
</P>
