<HEADLINE> IBM to Stop Sponsor Olympics after Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
IBM, which has cooperated with the IOC for 40 years, was widely
criticized for problems with the results service at the 1996
Atlanta Games.
</P>
<P>
Greg Ellevsen, IBM Australia's manager for corporate
communications, told local press that the company made this
decision because the costs were becoming too high and that the IOC
wanted a separate Internet provider.
</P>
<P>
Ellevsen said IBM informed the IOC of its decision on Friday
"and they understand, it was all very amicable."
</P>
<P>
Jim Sloman, acting chief executive of the Sydney Organizing
Committee for the Olympic Games (SOCOG), said on Friday that they
believe IBM would provide outstanding information technology for
the 2000 Games.  
