<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Jewllers Eye Tanzanian Gems Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan jewellers are
flocking into Tanzania which has abundant mineral resources, to
make profit out of gems business.
</P>
<P>
A Sri Lankan company SM Gems, for example, plans to invest
some 200,000 U.S. Dollars every month in buying Tanzanite, a
semi-precious stone unique to Tanzania, Business Times reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
SM Gems president Sony Punjabi, during a recent visit to
Tanzania, told the paper that his company will also tap the
potential of other gems.
</P>
<P>
Punjabi said that his company, based in Hong Kong, is seeking
permission from the Tanzanian Ministry of Energy and Minerals to
do business straight with local miners and dealers.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to set up a small lepidary center in the
northern town of Arusha, as well as to help local miners to grasp
the technology of cutting and polishing stones in a bid to
increase their values.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan businessmen used to purchase Tanzanian gems either
through Germany, Hong Kong, Thailand or through individual
suppliers.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the Tanzanian Ministry of Energy
and Minerals#,the east African country currently exports gems
worth 15 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, through cutting and polishing the gems at home and
marketing the export value may climb up to 45 million US Dollars
annually, the source added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
