<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More HIV Infections, AIDS Cases Reported in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 61 persons were
found positive for the HIV antibody test in the second quarter
this year, bringing the cumulative number of reported HIV
infections to 1,066, Hong Kong's Health Department said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-seven AIDS cases were reported in the same period,
leading to a total number of 349 confirmed cases since 1985,
according to the department.
</P>
<P>
The numbers of HIV infections and AIDS reported in the quarter
are the highest ever received in a single quarter since
surveillance system was established in 1984.
</P>
<P>
For the second quarter, the ratio of reported male to female
HIV infections is 3 to 1, data from the department showed.
</P>
<P>
Among the 61 new infections, 42 were sexually acquired with
heterosexual contact which remains the major route of
transmission. Five of them admitted themselves to be homosexuals
and one was an injecting drug user. Two of them were babies who
acquired the infection from their mothers.
</P>
<P>
As for the remaining 11 cases, the route of transmission was
not known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
