<HEADLINE> Germany to Donate Mozambique $15M </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany has decided to donate 15
million U.S. Dollars to Mozambique in four financial agreements
signed between the two governments.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican Financial Minister Leonardo Simao and German
Ambassador to Maputo Rolrudiger Zirpel signed the pacts here
Thursday, the Noticias newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Of the donation, three million U.S. Dollars will be used for
technological studies, five million U.S. Dollars will go to
the feasibility study of the expanded development
of Zambezi River, 1.5 million U.S. Dollars for the rehabilitation
of roads and the rest will be for the
restoration of the electricity transmission networks in northern
cities of Nampula and Nacala.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Mozambique and Germany last August held
talks on the financial and technological cooperation between the
two nations.
</P>
<P>
The German government pledged to donate 15 million U.S.
Dollars for financial cooperation and provide 20 million U.S.
Dollars in technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
The financial cooperation involved the Bank of Mozambique and
ministries of industry, trade, tourism, mines and energy,
transport and communications, and public works and housing.
</P>
<P>
For technical assistance projects, the German government
promised to support the Mozambican Institution of Rural
Development, the University of Eduardo Mondlane and ministries of
education, transport and communications, planning and finance,
labor, health and state administration.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Germany has been providing support for the southern
African country in removing land mines and lobbying for debt
relief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
