<HEADLINE> CD Postpones to Decide on Fissile Material </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Conference on Disarmament (CD)
has postponed to decide establishing an ad hoc committee on the
prohibition of production of fissile material for nuclear purposes
till next Tuesday, diplomatic sources said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 61-member conference had originally planned to make the
decision at a plenary session here Friday. But the Israeli
delegation told the conference that it needed more time to assess the
situation.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Jerusalem quoted Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu as saying that his government was carefully weighing its
response to the CD initiative.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, conference Chairman Mykola Maimeskul of Ukraine said
he was optimistic that the conference was "quite close" to
reaching consensus on setting up the committee to launch fresh talks
on a Fissile Material Cut-off Treaty (FMCT).
</P>
<P>
The CD members resumed on July 27 for the third and final part of
the 1998 session which will end on September 9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
