<HEADLINE> Australian Shares Close Slightly Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed slightly weaker in Sydney Friday with little inspiration
emerging from overseas markets to offset a generally nervous
environment.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index finished 3.4 points lower at 2,599.0
after vacillating between a positive and negative movement, with
relatively low volumes.
</P>
<P>
"The sentiment overall is still fairly negative, there wasn't
much direction there at all today," Sam Panetta from Shaw
Stockbroking said.
</P>
<P>
"The international markets are volatile and negative and our
market is just being very wary of that," he said.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index shed 1.2 points to 4,586.0.
</P>
<P>
The major banks all finished relatively steady, with Westpac
bank shedding one cent to 10.15 Australian dollars, National
Australia Bank up 6.7 cents to 22.247 Australian dollars, the
Commonwealth Bank of Australia down four cents at 19.91 Australian
dollars and ANZ bank six cents weaker at 10.06 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index was 5.9 points lower at 992.4.
</P>
<P>
Diversified resources bellwether BHP dropped 20 cents to 13.20
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index finished down 4.7 points at 994.0 points as the
bullion price dropped to 286.60 U.S. dollars per ounce compared to
Thursday's close of 287.95 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 258.05 million shares worth 484.6 million
U.S. dollars, with falls outnumbering rises 522 to 454. 
</P>
