<HEADLINE> Chinese Citizens Concerned about Wild Animals, Survey Shows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A majority of Chinese citizens
are deeply concerned about the treatment of wild animals and
actively support environmental protection efforts in China,
according to survey results disclosed today by Beijing Youth
Daily.
</P>
<P>
The survey of 1,738 people in Beijing and Shanghai shows that
most people like animals and are interested in watching TV
programs about them.
</P>
<P>
Some 85-to-90 percent of the respondents said that cats, dogs
and birds can become friends of mankind, and 90 percent of those
surveyed expressed strong indignation for people who mistreat
animals.
</P>
<P>
And 63.3 percent of those surveyed agree that animals can be
used for entertainment such as in a circus.
</P>
<P>
Regarding nourishment, 89.4 percent of the respondents said
that they will not use products made through mistreating animals;
83.7 percent said they will not use medicine made in the same way
and 27.8 percent said that they would not use the medicines even
to save their lives.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, 47.2 percent of the respondents like
to use products made of plants, and only 4 percent like to use
products using animals as raw material.
</P>
<P>
Almost all those surveyed, accounting for 96 percent, agree
that those who mistreat wild animals and endangered species should
be punished according to law.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that 96 percent of the respondents know
China's law on wildlife protection and 55.5 percent of them know
related international law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
