<HEADLINE> Pak National Assembly Condemns Indian Firing on LoC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's National Assembly
Standing Committee on Foreign Affairs Friday condemned the
unprovoked Indian shelling on civilians from across the Line of
Control (LoC) in disputed Kashmir area.
</P>
<P>
The committee urged the international community to take note of
India's aggressive designs.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the committee Abdul Waheed told a press conference
that the committee has adopted a resolution strongly condemning
the unprovoked Indian aggression as well as New Delhi's reign of
suppression in Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
"We have urged the international community to take note of
Indian brutal aggression against innocent civilians and stop its
reign of repression against Kashmiri men and commissions of
offense against women in the occupied Kashmir," he said.
</P>
<P>
The resolution urged the United Nations, Asia Watch and other
international bodies to stop New Delhi from carrying out its
brutalities and atrocities.
</P>
<P>
Waheed said that the heavy Indian firing on civilians in
Pakistan-held Kashmir this week also aims at pressurizing
Pakistan, the Kashmiris and Muslims living in India.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the recent unprovoked firing has proved that
Kashmir is a live dispute and needs international mediation for
peace and security in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
