<DOCNO> XIE19980807.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Gas Field Found in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, August 7 (Xinhua)-- A large natural gas field,
estimated to have gas reserves of more than 100 billion cubic
meters, has been discovered in the Junggar Basin of northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Tests have shown that the field has a 59-meter oil layer,
covering an area of more than 1,000 square kilometres, according
to a recent survey by the Xinjiang Petroleum Administration.
</P>
<P>
Located in the hinterlands of the Kurbantongut Desert, 150
kilometres from Karamay where the country's fourth largest oil
field is located, this gas field had shown signs of gas reserves
before, but bad weather in the desert stopped further exploration.
</P>
<P>
On August 3, one of the four wildcat wells began to gush oil
after it had been drilled to a depth of 4,438 meters, and its
daily output has reached more than 70,000 cubic meters and 46 tons
of light oil.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
