<DOCNO> XIE19980807.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong's Trade with Republic of Korea Rebounds in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Trade between east China's Shandong
Province and the Republic of Korea (ROK) rebounded in June, with
both exports and imports hitting this year's highs, according to
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's trade with ROK reached 390 million U.S. dollars in
June, a surge of 39 percent over May. Imports in June rocketed
47.6 percent to 270 million U.S. dollars, while exports jumped
22.3 percent to 120 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Surging crude oil and coal exports and rising imports by
overseas-funded enterprises were the major driving forces behind
the rebound of trade between Shandong and ROK, according to
experts.
</P>
<P>
After the introduction of new preferential tax policies at the
beginning of this year, ROK invested 130 million U.S. dollars in
equipment and materials in Shandong in the first half of this
year, a jump of 82.5 percent from the corresponding period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's imports from ROK include rubber, corn, pulp,
plastics, electronics, automatic digital processing equipment,
steel and refined oil, while exports include crude oil, cement,
raw materials, textiles and garments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
