<HEADLINE> American Insurance Firm Aims High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The American International
Assurance Co. Ltd. has vowed to be one of the most welcome
insurance firms in this economic and financial center of China.
</P>
<P>
"We will strive to do better, to be one of the best insurance
companies in Shanghai," said Nysco Shu, general manager of the
American insurer, in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
American International, which was present in Shanghai as early
as 1931, became the first licensed overseas insurance company in
this metropolis in 1992. In May of this year, American
International moved into the building that housed it decades ago.
</P>
<P>
American International's insurance business has been growing
steadily in Shanghai, with premiums in the first half of this year
up 30 percent from the comparable period of last year, according
to Shu.
</P>
<P>
He voiced his hope that more overseas insurance companies would
be allowed to do business in Shanghai and they should compete with
each other in insurance products and services.
</P>
<P>
"Our operation in Shanghai has enabled us to see the huge
potential of the Chinese insurance market and I personally hope
that the Chinese authorities will consider opening more cities to
overseas insurance companies," Shu said.
</P>
<P>
China currently allows a limited number of overseas insurance
companies to sell policies only in Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
American International now has nearly 400 employees and more
than 3,000 sales agents in Shanghai. Its customers exceeds
500,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
