<HEADLINE> Russia Reinforcing Troops on Russia-Latvia Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia is reinforcing its troops
on its border with Latvia as Latvia unilaterally defined the border
line in July, said Russia's Federal Border Service director
Nikolai Bordyuzha on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Latvia's move will not affect Russia's territory and security,
Bordyuzha said, adding Russian frontier troops will protect the border
and never have it changed.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two nations got seriously strained twice
this year, first by clashes between Russian-speaking Latvians and
local police in Rica on March 3 and, then by Russia-exerted
economic pressure on Latvia in April because of an explosion near
the Russian embassy in Latvia. 
