<HEADLINE> China Urging Companies To Participate In APEC Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese vice-minister of the State
Economic and Trade Commission, Chen Bangzhu, has urged the
country's businesses to develop ideas for technology exchanges at
the 2nd Asia-Pacific Economic Conference's Technology Conference
and Fair, scheduled for this east China city from October 8 to 14.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the conference is to develop overseas markets,
draw investment from overseas, stimulate domestic and overseas
market demand, and promote China's economic growth. It is expected
to be a good place to exhibit the confidence Chinese enterprises
have in overcoming the impact of the Asian financial turmoil, Chen
said.
</P>
<P>
All 21 APEC member states have plans to attend the fair and
have reserved 604 booths, 356 of for overseas firms, involving
2,700 entrepreneurs, according to the organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
