<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qingdao Uses Overseas Funds to Develop Animal Husbandry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- This major city of east China's
Shandong Province has developed its animal husbandry by using
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Six large overseas-funded animal husbandry projects were
approved in the first half of this year, with pledged overseas
investment totaling 152 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The projects cover the production of animal feed, milk
refining, the development of breeding centers and animal farms and
the processing of table chickens.
</P>
<P>
Investors came from such areas as Taiwan, the United States and
Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
