<HEADLINE> China Folk Arts Festival in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The industrial and commercial
center of China, Shanghai, is now preparing for the Fourth China
International Folk Art Festival, scheduled for August 25.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day festival, Chinese visitors will treated to
performances by opera and dance groups from nine countries,
including Poland, France, Span, Italy, Croatia, Russia, the
Republic of Korea (ROK), and Japan,
</P>
<P>
With the theme "develop folk arts, promote friendship and
peace," the festival will increase exchanges between artists from
different nations and enrich the daily lives of the Chinese people.
</P>
