<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sartaj Aziz Takes over as Pakistan's FM Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Sartaj Aziz, former Pakistani
finance minister, formally took over the charge as foreign
minister Friday.
</P>
<P>
Aziz replaced Gohar Ayub Khan, who has been redesignated as
minister for water and power.
</P>
<P>
Gohar tendered his resignation in April requesting Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif to change his post as the foreign minister
which, he said, kept him away from his electorates.
</P>
<P>
Aziz served as finance minister from August 1990 to July 1993
during the first government led by Sharif and was given the same
portfolio in Sharif's new cabinet sworn in in February 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
