<HEADLINE> Chinese Education Enjoys Supports from World Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- China has so far received loans
totaling 1.4 billion U.S. dollars from the World Bank for
educational reforms.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education reports that more than 100,000
Chinese institutes of higher learning and primary and secondary
schools have enjoyed support from the World Bank. In 1981, the
World Bank made its first loan to Chinese education.
</P>
<P>
Since then, 7,395 people have gone abroad for advanced
training, 252,000 teachers have received on-job training, and
1,517 education specialists from overeseas have been invited to
China to help improve teaching quality.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education is now working closely with the World
Bank to improve the educational system and reform the teaching
curriculum.  
</P>
