<HEADLINE> ADF Rebels Kill 33 in Western Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of Uganda's Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) killed at least 33 people including
government soldiers in the western district of Kasese, Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
This surprise attack came about hours before Ugandan President
Yoweri Museveni's visit to the district, the New Vision paper
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
But the Press Secretary to the President, Hope Kivengere, told
Xinhua in a telephone interview Friday morning that this did not
prevent the president from going there and the president spent
the whole day in the west Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Jonathan Tigali, a Kyarumba sub-county chief
as saying that the ADF rebels attacked a government army unit at
about 3:00 p.m.(local time ).
</P>
<P>
James Kazini, the Acting Army Chief of Staff, said the rebels
launched two separate raids on Kyarumba and Ihandiro
sub-countyies.
</P>
<P>
He confirmed that some soldiers and a family of six were
killed but was non-committal about the number of rmldiers killed.
</P>
<P>
The strike by the rebels followed another invasion on Kasese
twon last Friday at which 16 people were killed, 26 vehicles and
hotel rooms burnt and other property destroyed.
</P>
<P>
While addressing the local council in Kasese Thursday,
Museveni promised to use big guns against the increasingly
rampant rebel activities in the area.
</P>
<P>
"There will be adequate capacity to fight the ADF rebels
during the night and day," the president was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The president reassured the foreign and local investors in the
area that the safety of their lives and property will be
guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors in Kasese and expatriates in the
construction companies for the Kasese Cobalt Processing Project
and Hima Cement Factory had threatened to leave the area for fear
of rebel attacks. 
</P>
