<HEADLINE> China to Telecast Famous River Waves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China will for the first time
telecast live the magical waves of the Qiantang River in this
city, capital of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The broadcast will occur during the '98 International Qiantang
River-Wave Watching Festival, scheduled for October 6-10.
</P>
<P>
The magnificent scene of the river's huge waves can be viewed
on TV across China and in many parts of the world, according to the
provincial tourism bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau also said that the live telecast will be jointly
presented by China Central Television Station and the Zhejiang
Television Station. 
</P>
