<P>
Among the killed were Colorado Agriculture Commissioner David
L. Ford, 50, his brothers, Doug, 49, and Gene, 48, and Gene Ford's
son, John, 20.
</P>
<P>
The brothers were scattering the ashes of their mother, Lenore
Ford, when their Cessna 210 went down near a private fishing club
about 500 kilometers southeast of Denver.
</P>
<P>
The mother died in a car accident about six weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitness told authorities the plane cartwheeled into the
trees shortly before 8 a.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
