<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Take Part in BIMST-EC Meeting in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will participate in the
Economic Ministers' Meeting of a new regional grouping, the
BIMST-EC (Bangladesh, India, Myanmar, Sri Lanka and
Thailand-Economic Cooperation), due to begin in Bangkok, Thailand,
later Friday.
</P>
<P>
The BIMST-EC is a sub-regional economic grouping originally
formed in June 1997 with four countries bordering the Bay of
Bengal and its membership was extended to Myanmar in August the
same year.
</P>
<P>
Minister at the Office of the Chairman of the State Peace and
Development Council Brigadier-General Abel will head the
delegation representing Myanmar for the meeting, the official
newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
It will be the second time for Myanmar to attend the BIMST-EC
ministerial meeting since the country joined the grouping.
</P>
<P>
A special ministerial meeting of the grouping, held in Bangkok
in December 1997, agreed to strengthen cooperation in the fields
of trade, investment, transport and communications, energy,
tourism and fishery among the member countries.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar, together with Thailand, is a member of both the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations and the BIMST-EC, thus
becoming a gateway for the two groupings to link South and
Southeast Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
