<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Foreign currency deposits in
Uruguay increased to 8,097.4 million U.S. dollars at the end of
June from the 7,543 million dollars at the end of 1997, said the
the country's Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
One third of the deposits is in the state-owned Banco de la
Republica and the rest in private banks.
</P>
<P>
