<HEADLINE> China Exports Fuel Injectors to France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The First group of 10,000 EV6
fuel injectors produced by the Shanghai United Automobile
Electronics Co. Ltd. has recently been exported to France.
</P>
<P>
The company said the injectors will be used in manufacturing
Citroen and Peugeot automobiles. This deal has put an end to
China's previous zero-level in exporting high-tech automobile
electronical products such as fuel injector systems.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai United Automobile Electronics Co. Ltd. is a joint
venture started by ten Chinese companies and a German company with
an investment of 2.668 billion yuan. The company mainly produces
advanced gasoline-flow engine control systems for automobiles, and
has an annual production capacity of 500,000 units.
</P>
<P>
These fuel injectors are used in manufacturing the China-made
Santana, Jetta, and Citroen-Fukang cars, and are also used by
Toyota Automobile Engines Co. Ltd. of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The use of these advanced systems can reduce harmful automobile
exhaust by 50 percent, lower fuel consumption and improve overall
performance. Auto gas exhaust may be reduced by as high as 95
percent if catalytic technology is also applied, said one of the
joint venture's engineers.
</P>
<P>
This joint venture, which now has many orders from a number of
overseas companies, will export 370,000 fuel injectors this year,
and 700,000 in 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980807.0275 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Village Election Held in Spite of Heavy Rain (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two candidates, both of whom were nominated by more than
10 villagers, began to make their speeches.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yuguo, holding a stick in his right hand and an umbrella in
the other, pushed his way through the crowd to the rostrum. During
his speech he asked the other candidate to withdraw.
</P>
<P>
Liu, 39, is a village doctor with a high school education. His
speech was a hit, winning applause from the audience five times.
</P>
<P>
Prolonged applause broke out at the end of his speech when Liu
said firmly: "Democracy must be practiced widely in the daily work
of the village committee. The financial report shall be open to
the public. A villagers advisory council will be set up..." Many
people waved their umbrellas in the rain to show their support.
</P>
<P>
Li Xuewen, the other candidate, also received some clapping
when he addressed the crowd.
</P>
<P>
After their speeches, the two men answered questions from the
villagers.
</P>
<P>
All the voters were divided into five groups. One by one, they
picked up the ballots by showing their voter-registration cards
and filled them out at the designated desk. Scrutinized by two
polling observers, the completed ballots were then put into the
boxes.
</P>
<P>
A mobile ballot box was used to get the ballots from door to
door for old and disabled villagers.
</P>
<P>
Observers and vote-counters were chosen by the public after the
voting. With 1,121 valid ballots tallied, Liu Yuguo beat his
opponent by the overwhelming majority of 809 votes.
</P>
<P>
At noon, people began to leave the square in the rain, wearing
excited smiles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
