<DOCNO> XIE19980807.0277 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia's Emerald Exports Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's emerald
export dropped 45.9 percent to 37.2 million U.S. dollars in the
first six months of this year, compared with the same period last
year, says the National Statistics Administrative Department
(DANE).
</P>
<P>
Of the last six months, March was the most active with export
of 1 million carats fetching 8.3 million dollars while May had the
least movement with export of 731,725 carats for a little more
than 4 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Colombia exported more cut stones than emeralds in the rough in
the period.
</P>
<P>
The United States was the largest buyer of Colombian emeralds,
importing 3.1 million carats at a cost of 17.9 million dollars in
the first half of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Colombia is the biggest producer and supplier of emeralds in
the world. The production center is in the department of Boyaca.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
