<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Anhui Province Reports Good Early Rice Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has reaped
a good early rice harvest despite severe flooding, according to
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Anhui's output of early rice totaled 1.95 billion kilos this
year, which translates to 5,037.5 kilos per hectare, slightly
higher than the per-unit yield last year.
</P>
<P>
The provincial agricultural department said that Anhui's
acreage of early rice this year was 387,000 hectares, about 13,000
less than last year.
</P>
<P>
In late June, when early rice entered a critical growth period,
Anhui was hit by a spell of torrential rains, causing great damage
to agricultural production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
