<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan authorities have
closed part of the border in Cabinda Province since late Tuesday
in response to a request by Kinshasa, a military source disclosed
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As the military situation is worsened in eastern Congo (K),
the administration at Muanda town in lower Congo Province asked
Angola to close the border of Yema, the source said.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Kinshasa has returned to peace after armed
clashes broke out there on Sunday night and Monday morning, but
fighting in other parts of the country such as the east remains
fierce so far.
</P>
