It is reported that senior Angolan officers and the governor
of Cabinda province went Wednesday to Yema to be acquainted with
the situation there.
</P>
<P>
A source from the Congolese town of Muanda said atmosphere
there is relatively calm and that situation is under control.
</P>
<P>
The border post at Yema is a major port of trade between
citizens of the two countries and it is 35 kilometers away from
Cabinda city. 
