defected and rebels have allegedly seized the eastern town of
Bukavu.
</P>
<P>
Government officials of DRC acknowledged that Bukavu had
fallen to a Tutsi-led dissident faction of the new Congolese army
after two days of heavy fighting but accused troops from
estranged ally Rwanda's Tutsi-dominated army of taking part.
</P>
<P>
The sudden change of situation in this central African country
has immediately attracted the attention of its close neighbors as
well as many other countries around the world. 
